1
00:00:10.955 --> 00:00:12.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sell at 20.

2
00:00:12.115 --> 00:00:13.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is that a joke?

3
00:00:13.595 --> 00:00:15.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do I look like I'm joking?

4
00:00:16.354 --> 00:00:17.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

5
00:00:21.112 --> 00:00:22.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She has him.

6
00:00:22.674 --> 00:00:24.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-She's down 50 strips.
-Not for long.

7
00:00:25.432 --> 00:00:27.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What makes you so sure?

8
00:00:27.292 --> 00:00:29.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, Jadzia's playing a very deep game.

9
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Her strategy will become
apparent any moment now.

10
00:00:32.409 --> 00:00:33.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see.

11
00:00:35.370 --> 00:00:38.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have absolutely no idea
how this game is played, do you?

12
00:00:41.088 --> 00:00:42.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-No.
-( chuckles )

13
00:00:42.528 --> 00:00:44.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I have developed
a new appreciation for it.

14
00:00:44.749 --> 00:00:47.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh? Since when?
-Since I married a Tongo player.

15
00:00:48.785 --> 00:00:50.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But one thing I am certain about--

16
00:00:50.685 --> 00:00:52.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She will defeat the Ferengi bartender.

17
00:00:53.045 --> 00:00:55.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know about that.
Quark's on a roll.

18
00:00:55.803 --> 00:00:58.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In the last month,
he's won 206 straight games.

19
00:01:01.542 --> 00:01:03.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you care to make
a wager on the outcome?

20
00:01:03.781 --> 00:01:06.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, I wouldn't want to bet
against a man's wife.

21
00:01:06.222 --> 00:01:08.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, if you are afraid--
-Name your stakes.

22
00:01:10.179 --> 00:01:12.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One bottle of bloodwine
against one bottle of scotch whiskey.

23
00:01:13.618 --> 00:01:14.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Done.

24
00:01:16.857 --> 00:01:20.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A sale at 50 and a purchase at 100.

25
00:01:21.675 --> 00:01:24.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Pretty big talk for
a lady who's lost 50 strips.

26
00:01:25.016 --> 00:01:26.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you afraid I can't cover my bets?

27
00:01:27.811 --> 00:01:28.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perish the thought!

28
00:01:28.133 --> 00:01:31.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I just hate to kick
somebody when they're down.

29
00:01:31.393 --> 00:01:34.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll buy at 100... and confront.

30
00:01:35.772 --> 00:01:38.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if you're gonna kick me,
I'm gonna have to kick back.

31
00:01:38.332 --> 00:01:39.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: unbelievable.

32
00:01:39.813 --> 00:01:41.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( exclaims in native langauge )

33
00:01:43.369 --> 00:01:45.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I like my bloodwine
very young and very sweet.

34
00:01:47.128 --> 00:01:49.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is he a friend of yours?
-Just a fan.

35
00:01:49.907 --> 00:01:52.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid I'm going to have
to disappoint all your fans.

36
00:01:55.346 --> 00:01:56.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A full consortium?

37
00:01:56.705 --> 00:01:58.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
207.

38
00:01:58.625 --> 00:02:01.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A single malt,
preferably something from the highlands.

39
00:02:02.223 --> 00:02:03.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will need some time.

40
00:02:03.743 --> 00:02:05.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, your credit's good.

41
00:02:08.541 --> 00:02:11.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoo, 207 straight.

42
00:02:11.819 --> 00:02:13.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: 36 strips of gold press latinum.

43
00:02:16.500 --> 00:02:18.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Did you lose a bet?
-It is of no consequence.

44
00:02:18.778 --> 00:02:19.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry about that.

45
00:02:23.697 --> 00:02:26.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would rather lose a bet on you
than win on someone else.

46
00:02:27.536 --> 00:02:29.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh, good response.

47
00:02:37.533 --> 00:02:39.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you still running
that drill tomorrow afternoon?

48
00:02:39.692 --> 00:02:40.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was planning to. Why?

49
00:02:41.052 --> 00:02:43.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because I wanted to recalibrate
the external sensors

50
00:02:43.951 --> 00:02:46.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
before the night watch comes on duty.

51
00:02:47.189 --> 00:02:49.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should be done by 1600 hours.

52
00:02:49.399 --> 00:02:50.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I think that'll work.

53
00:02:52.398 --> 00:02:56.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, the <i>Sutherland </i>is going to
be here the day after tomorrow and...

54
00:03:12.822 --> 00:03:14.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You were saying?
-Nothing.

55
00:03:20.380 --> 00:03:23.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't feel like talking anymore.

56
00:03:43.054 --> 00:03:43.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beep )
<i>-Kira to Worf.</i>

57
00:03:52.290 --> 00:03:53.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf here.

58
00:03:53.610 --> 00:03:56.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
KIRA:<i> Sorry to bother you, Commander,</i>
<i>but I need to see you and Jadzia</i>

59
00:03:56.610 --> 00:03:57.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>in the Captain's office, immediately.</i>

60
00:03:58.690 --> 00:04:00.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're on our way.

61
00:04:07.847 --> 00:04:09.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia... Get up.

62
00:04:09.966 --> 00:04:11.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm coming!

63
00:04:11.965 --> 00:04:13.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey!

64
00:04:13.404 --> 00:04:15.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't have a lot of time,
so I'll get right to it.

65
00:04:15.755 --> 00:04:16.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For the last two months,

66
00:04:17.283 --> 00:04:20.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet has been receiving
military intelligence

67
00:04:20.044 --> 00:04:21.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
from a Cardassian operative.

68
00:04:21.561 --> 00:04:23.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That operative has now sent
an emergency signal

69
00:04:23.942 --> 00:04:27.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
indicating he needs to speak to someone
in a face-to-face conversation.

70
00:04:27.781 --> 00:04:28.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In 13 hours,

71
00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:31.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he'll beam an encrypted
subspace transmission

72
00:04:31.380 --> 00:04:33.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to these coordinates in the badlands.

73
00:04:33.998 --> 00:04:34.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who is the operative?

74
00:04:35.197 --> 00:04:37.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Intelligence told me that
his name is Lasaran,

75
00:04:37.797 --> 00:04:39.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But that's all they'll say about him.

76
00:04:39.876 --> 00:04:43.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They did emphasize several times that
he is very important to them

77
00:04:43.698 --> 00:04:46.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and that we should send someone
to the badlands as soon as possible.

78
00:04:47.075 --> 00:04:49.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, with the <i>Defiant </i>gone,

79
00:04:49.173 --> 00:04:52.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and most of the runabouts off on exercises
with the Ninth Fleet...

80
00:04:52.592 --> 00:04:54.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We just volunteered for
a trip to the badlands.

81
00:04:54.672 --> 00:04:55.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Afraid so.

82
00:04:56.091 --> 00:04:58.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The <i>Shenandoah's </i>prepped
and ready to go on landing pad "A."

83
00:04:58.850 --> 00:04:59.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

84
00:07:11.570 --> 00:07:13.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-No.
-No?

85
00:07:13.070 --> 00:07:14.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
No, I'm not going to spend two weeks

86
00:07:14.830 --> 00:07:17.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
hiking across Vulcan's forge
in the middle of their summer.

87
00:07:17.589 --> 00:07:19.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I thought you always
wanted to see the forge.

88
00:07:19.569 --> 00:07:21.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
See it, yes. Honeymoon there, no.

89
00:07:22.587 --> 00:07:24.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, there's a mountain-climbing
expedition on Andor

90
00:07:24.648 --> 00:07:25.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
that caught my attention.

91
00:07:25.688 --> 00:07:28.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Worf... My love...

92
00:07:28.447 --> 00:07:29.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Let me make this very clear.

93
00:07:29.966 --> 00:07:31.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I do not want to spend my honeymoon

94
00:07:32.005 --> 00:07:35.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
climbing, hiking, sweating, bleeding,
or suffering in any way.

95
00:07:36.942 --> 00:07:39.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-All right, what do you want?
-Room service.

96
00:07:39.102 --> 00:07:40.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Room service?
-Room service.

97
00:07:40.102 --> 00:07:41.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want to be pampered.

98
00:07:41.262 --> 00:07:43.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want a staff to cater to our every whim.

99
00:07:43.601 --> 00:07:45.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want to be embarrassed
by the size of our room.

100
00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:49.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want a balcony with a view
that would make you want

101
00:07:49.041 --> 00:07:51.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
to break down and cry
from the sheer beauty of it all.

102
00:07:51.679 --> 00:07:55.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And I don't want to spend
one moment of our honeymoon

103
00:07:55.274 --> 00:07:56.434  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
suffering from anything

104
00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:59.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
except guilt about
our complete self-indulgence.

105
00:08:00.553 --> 00:08:01.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Risa.

106
00:08:01.896 --> 00:08:02.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not this time.

107
00:08:04.408 --> 00:08:06.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Welcome to Casperia Prime,

108
00:08:06.275 --> 00:08:08.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the vacation capital
of the Horvarian cluster.

109
00:08:12.773 --> 00:08:14.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have been planning this all along.

110
00:08:15.171 --> 00:08:17.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, it seemed fair.
You did plan the wedding.

111
00:08:19.091 --> 00:08:20.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very well. Room service.

112
00:08:20.630 --> 00:08:22.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Really?
-Really.

113
00:08:22.790 --> 00:08:23.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that was easy.

114
00:08:24.988 --> 00:08:26.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you want to fight over it?

115
00:08:26.829 --> 00:08:28.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. It's just...

116
00:08:28.388 --> 00:08:30.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't expect you
to surrender so quickly.

117
00:08:30.609 --> 00:08:32.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Surrender?
-Bad word.

118
00:08:32.216 --> 00:08:33.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Very bad.
-OK.

119
00:08:33.205 --> 00:08:37.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But you have to admit you've been
unusually...accommodating lately.

120
00:08:38.865 --> 00:08:39.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is wrong with that?

121
00:08:40.144 --> 00:08:41.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing. It's just...

122
00:08:42.143 --> 00:08:43.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unusual.

123
00:08:43.623 --> 00:08:44.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you feeling all right?

124
00:08:44.983 --> 00:08:46.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am a married man.

125
00:08:47.262 --> 00:08:50.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have to make certain...
adjustments in my lifestyle.

126
00:08:50.901 --> 00:08:52.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Adjustments?

127
00:08:52.971 --> 00:08:54.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf, you're practically easygoing.

128
00:08:54.501 --> 00:08:57.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's next, a sense of humor?

129
00:08:57.162 --> 00:08:57.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have a sense of humor.

130
00:08:59.762 --> 00:09:02.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
On the <i>Enterprise,</i>
I was considered to be quite amusing.

131
00:09:02.761 --> 00:09:04.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that must've been one dull ship.

132
00:09:04.896 --> 00:09:05.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That is a joke!

133
00:09:06.541 --> 00:09:07.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I get it.

134
00:09:07.416 --> 00:09:09.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is not funny, but I get it.

135
00:09:09.415 --> 00:09:12.015  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know if I can
get used to the new you.

136
00:09:12.095 --> 00:09:13.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's kind of eerie.

137
00:09:13.694 --> 00:09:16.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your problem is
you cannot accept change.

138
00:09:16.687 --> 00:09:19.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I can't accept change?
-That is correct.

139
00:09:19.406 --> 00:09:20.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you've got to be kidding.

140
00:09:20.912 --> 00:09:23.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've changed bodies six times, Worf.

141
00:09:23.132 --> 00:09:25.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but you are still
very set in your ways.

142
00:09:25.790 --> 00:09:27.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And look who's talking.

143
00:09:27.850 --> 00:09:31.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I do not have to sleep
on the same side of the bed every night,

144
00:09:31.909 --> 00:09:34.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or brush my hair exactly 50 strokes
every night,

145
00:09:34.848 --> 00:09:36.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or eat the same thing
for breakfast every day,

146
00:09:37.267 --> 00:09:39.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or read the last page of the book
before the beginning,

147
00:09:39.827 --> 00:09:41.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-or lift up--
-I get the point.

148
00:09:42.626 --> 00:09:45.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know how you can live
with someone so monotonous.

149
00:09:46.464 --> 00:09:47.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is not easy.

150
00:09:50.243 --> 00:09:51.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was a joke.

151
00:09:53.382 --> 00:09:56.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is going to be
a very, very long trip.

152
00:10:05.780 --> 00:10:06.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door chimes )

153
00:10:06.698 --> 00:10:07.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come in.

154
00:10:08.977 --> 00:10:10.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're not dressed.

155
00:10:10.977 --> 00:10:13.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is it time?
-1700 on the dot.

156
00:10:13.759 --> 00:10:14.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have the holosuite
for the next three hours,

157
00:10:14.695 --> 00:10:15.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we're going to
need every minute of it.

158
00:10:15.655 --> 00:10:17.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Three British agents have disappeared
in West Berlin.

159
00:10:18.035 --> 00:10:20.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, M.I. Five suspect
the Soviets were involved of course.

160
00:10:21.434 --> 00:10:24.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
However, the Americans
have intercepted a, uh...

161
00:10:23.793 --> 00:10:25.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing with a Tongo wheel?

162
00:10:25.633 --> 00:10:27.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm brushing up on my game.

163
00:10:27.472 --> 00:10:28.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You play Tongo?
-Sure.

164
00:10:30.311 --> 00:10:32.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I used to.

165
00:10:33.271 --> 00:10:35.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That is, I played the game once,
a long time ago,

166
00:10:35.789 --> 00:10:39.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with a Ferengi privateer
and a Romulan mercenary.

167
00:10:39.668 --> 00:10:40.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fascinating.

168
00:10:40.708 --> 00:10:44.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Anyway, the Americans have intercepted
a series of messages from Istanbul

169
00:10:44.387 --> 00:10:46.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to a remote island in the South Pacific

170
00:10:46.370 --> 00:10:47.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-which might indicate--
-Let's play a hand.

171
00:10:47.250 --> 00:10:47.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles...

172
00:10:47.949 --> 00:10:49.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Just one hand.
-Why?

173
00:10:49.829 --> 00:10:50.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need the practice.

174
00:10:50.670 --> 00:10:51.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

175
00:10:52.009 --> 00:10:53.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to beat Quark.

176
00:10:54.209 --> 00:10:54.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

177
00:10:55.470 --> 00:10:56.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Luck has nothing to do with it.

178
00:10:57.809 --> 00:11:00.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tongo is a game of strategy
and calculated risk.

179
00:11:00.809 --> 00:11:01.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't even know the rules.

180
00:11:01.889 --> 00:11:02.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, here.

181
00:11:03.189 --> 00:11:04.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right, let's play. I'll deal.

182
00:11:06.649 --> 00:11:10.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: <i>Shenandoah log: Stardate 51597.2.</i>

183
00:11:10.110 --> 00:11:12.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We have arrived </i>
<i>at the designated coordinates</i>

184
00:11:12.069 --> 00:11:14.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>near the badlands and are</i>
<i>awaiting the transmission from Lasaran.</i>

185
00:11:17.549 --> 00:11:18.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: This is it.

186
00:11:18.850 --> 00:11:20.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A very sophisticated encryption matrix.

187
00:11:21.289 --> 00:11:22.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoever he is, he's good.

188
00:11:25.889 --> 00:11:26.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Who are you?</i>

189
00:11:27.230 --> 00:11:29.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm Commander Worf. This is Commander Dax.

190
00:11:30.110 --> 00:11:32.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet Intelligence has sent us here
to receive your transmission.

191
00:11:33.129 --> 00:11:34.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A Klingon.</i>

192
00:11:34.889 --> 00:11:36.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Why did they have to send a Klingon?</i>

193
00:11:37.370 --> 00:11:39.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm a Trill.
Does that make you feel any better?

194
00:11:39.769 --> 00:11:43.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-Are you trying to be funny?</i>
-Oh, not at all. He's the funny one.

195
00:11:43.629 --> 00:11:46.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What is it you want?
<i>-We'll get to that in a minute.</i>

196
00:11:46.269 --> 00:11:48.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>First, I have something </i>
<i>that you want, badly...</i>

197
00:11:49.009 --> 00:11:50.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Information on the Founders.</i>

198
00:11:50.889 --> 00:11:53.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I know how many of them</i>
<i>there are in the Alpha Quadrant,</i>

199
00:11:53.470 --> 00:11:55.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>where they are, and what they're doing.</i>

200
00:11:55.970 --> 00:11:58.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We're listening.
<i>-I'm sure you are.</i>

201
00:11:58.149 --> 00:11:59.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Now let's talk about what I want.</i>

202
00:11:59.809 --> 00:12:01.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I want out, now.</i>

203
00:12:01.549 --> 00:12:02.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You want to defect.

204
00:12:02.750 --> 00:12:05.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Vorta advisor here </i>
<i>is getting suspicious...</i>

205
00:12:05.409 --> 00:12:06.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Asking questions,</i>

206
00:12:06.429 --> 00:12:09.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>making a lot of routine </i>
<i>security checks in my section.</i>

207
00:12:09.110 --> 00:12:10.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I can't stay here any longer.</i>

208
00:12:11.009 --> 00:12:11.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: Very well.

209
00:12:11.850 --> 00:12:13.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We will relay your message
to Starfleet Intelligence

210
00:12:13.829 --> 00:12:15.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they will arrange to bring you out.

211
00:12:15.789 --> 00:12:17.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I can't wait for them </i>
<i>to make arrangements.</i>

212
00:12:17.709 --> 00:12:21.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>In 15 minutes, I am leaving here</i>
<i>for the Dominion base on Soukara,</i>

213
00:12:21.689 --> 00:12:23.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and I have a feeling </i>
<i>this is going to be the last time</i>

214
00:12:23.649 --> 00:12:25.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>that they let me leave Cardassia Prime.</i>

215
00:12:25.590 --> 00:12:28.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So, I need to take advantage </i>
<i>of this opportunity.</i>

216
00:12:29.649 --> 00:12:31.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Soukara is inside
Dominion-controlled space.

217
00:12:31.569 --> 00:12:35.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It will not be easy to make a rendezvous
near that planet without being detected.

218
00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:37.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Don't work your brain too hard, Klingon.</i>

219
00:12:37.389 --> 00:12:38.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I've taken care of everything.</i>

220
00:12:38.909 --> 00:12:42.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Three days from now </i>
<i>at exactly 1730 hours local time,</i>

221
00:12:42.870 --> 00:12:45.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I will leave the base </i>
<i>and walk into the jungle.</i>

222
00:12:46.171 --> 00:12:49.093  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It'll be at least two days</i>
<i>before they know I'm missing.</i>

223
00:12:49.229 --> 00:12:51.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>All you have to do </i>
<i>is get me off the planet.</i>

224
00:12:52.441 --> 00:12:54.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Now, there are transporter scramblers </i>
<i>protecting Soukara</i>

225
00:12:55.587 --> 00:12:57.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>so you can't beam me aboard your ship.</i>

226
00:12:57.347 --> 00:13:01.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You're going to have to land</i>
<i>and meet me at a rendezvous point on foot.</i>

227
00:13:01.966 --> 00:13:04.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I am sending you all </i>
<i>the information you'll need</i>

228
00:13:04.427 --> 00:13:06.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to avoid the Dominion sensors </i>
<i>on the ground.</i>

229
00:13:07.704 --> 00:13:08.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Follow my instructions.</i>

230
00:13:09.343 --> 00:13:12.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Meet me at this rendezvous point</i>
<i>and have a ship waiting.</i>

231
00:13:14.877 --> 00:13:17.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've got the information.
It looks pretty thorough.

232
00:13:17.061 --> 00:13:18.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will need time to study these plans.

233
00:13:18.841 --> 00:13:21.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You haven't been listening. </i>
<i>I don't have time.</i>

234
00:13:21.122 --> 00:13:23.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Once I leave here, </i>
<i>I can't contact you again.</i>

235
00:13:23.839 --> 00:13:25.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I have to know if you're</i>
<i>going to be there or not,</i>

236
00:13:25.960 --> 00:13:27.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and I have to know now!</i>

237
00:13:30.357 --> 00:13:31.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will be there.

238
00:13:32.696 --> 00:13:33.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>How far I've fallen... </i>( sighs )

239
00:13:35.276 --> 00:13:37.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Risking my life on the word of a Klingon.</i>

240
00:13:38.715 --> 00:13:40.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Three days. Don't be late.</i>

241
00:13:55.590 --> 00:13:59.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right.
I'll buy at 30 with sales at 35.

242
00:13:59.917 --> 00:14:02.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Buy at 35, sell at 150
and index the margin at 10%.

243
00:14:03.507 --> 00:14:05.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Index the margin?
-Miles, give it up.

244
00:14:05.748 --> 00:14:07.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-This just isn't your game.
-We'll see about that.

245
00:14:08.227 --> 00:14:09.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

246
00:14:10.106 --> 00:14:11.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

247
00:14:13.114 --> 00:14:14.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you realize

248
00:14:14.433 --> 00:14:17.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that Quark has won
207 straight games of Tongo?

249
00:14:17.583 --> 00:14:18.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So?

250
00:14:19.062 --> 00:14:20.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, someone has to beat him.

251
00:14:20.083 --> 00:14:21.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And that someone is you?

252
00:14:21.512 --> 00:14:22.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

253
00:14:22.832 --> 00:14:25.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, for one thing, you can't play Tongo.

254
00:14:26.081 --> 00:14:26.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

255
00:14:28.200 --> 00:14:29.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans ) Damn!

256
00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:32.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Had enough?
-Not by a long shot.

257
00:14:32.439 --> 00:14:35.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Miles, at this rate,
it's going to take you another 20 years

258
00:14:35.081 --> 00:14:36.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to be ready to take on Quark.

259
00:14:36.520 --> 00:14:37.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One more.

260
00:14:38.509 --> 00:14:39.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Why are you
so determined to beat him?

261
00:14:40.440 --> 00:14:41.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's the challenge.
-A challenge?

262
00:14:42.479 --> 00:14:43.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Isn't it enough?

263
00:14:43.838 --> 00:14:45.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, why do you think
I became an engineer, eh?

264
00:14:46.086 --> 00:14:47.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The challenge.

265
00:14:47.574 --> 00:14:49.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What do you think's kept me
kayaking down the same river

266
00:14:49.874 --> 00:14:52.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
week after week for the last seven years?

267
00:14:52.352 --> 00:14:54.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The challenge.

268
00:14:54.413 --> 00:14:56.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why would I keep playing darts
against somebody

269
00:14:56.394 --> 00:14:59.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with a genetically engineered
hand/eye coordination, huh?

270
00:14:59.872 --> 00:15:02.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The challenge.
-Exactly.

271
00:15:04.431 --> 00:15:06.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have to do something
to keep my mind off the fact

272
00:15:06.310 --> 00:15:08.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that Keiko's been away
for the last six months.

273
00:15:10.828 --> 00:15:11.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hold on.

274
00:15:13.067 --> 00:15:15.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe I can't beat Quark...

275
00:15:16.286 --> 00:15:17.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you can.

276
00:15:18.285 --> 00:15:20.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You and that genetically
engineered brain of yours.

277
00:15:20.725 --> 00:15:22.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Me? I've only just learned
how to play the game.

278
00:15:22.804 --> 00:15:24.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, in about 10 seconds flat!

279
00:15:26.083 --> 00:15:27.124  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can do it, Julian.

280
00:15:27.682 --> 00:15:28.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can beat him.

281
00:15:29.001 --> 00:15:30.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"We"?

282
00:15:30.811 --> 00:15:31.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're talking about me.

283
00:15:32.361 --> 00:15:35.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, well, you're good at calculation
but a little weak on strategy.

284
00:15:35.752 --> 00:15:37.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll be your coach.
-No, thank you.

285
00:15:38.279 --> 00:15:39.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Think of it as a challenge.

286
00:15:40.039 --> 00:15:41.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's your obsession, Miles, not mine.

287
00:15:41.898 --> 00:15:42.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do it for the latinum.

288
00:15:43.138 --> 00:15:44.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nice try.

289
00:15:44.297 --> 00:15:47.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do it for the satisfaction
of the look on Quark's face

290
00:15:48.056 --> 00:15:51.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when he's beaten at a game of Tongo
by a lowly "hu-man."

291
00:15:52.815 --> 00:15:53.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Deal the cards.

292
00:16:03.072 --> 00:16:04.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are approaching the Soukara system.

293
00:16:05.031 --> 00:16:06.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand by to bring us out of warp.

294
00:16:06.471 --> 00:16:08.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now.

295
00:16:09.270 --> 00:16:10.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There is an asteroid field directly ahead.

296
00:16:11.009 --> 00:16:11.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what we want.

297
00:16:11.968 --> 00:16:14.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Dominion's sensor grid
in the system has three gaps

298
00:16:14.530 --> 00:16:16.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they're all in that asteroid field.

299
00:16:21.608 --> 00:16:22.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: Want me to slow down?

300
00:16:23.006 --> 00:16:24.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, unless you think you should.

301
00:16:24.965 --> 00:16:26.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not at all. In fact, we could go faster.

302
00:16:26.924 --> 00:16:28.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By all means.

303
00:16:28.844 --> 00:16:30.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh! A man after my own heart.

304
00:16:45.059 --> 00:16:45.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Most impressive.

305
00:16:46.638 --> 00:16:48.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nothing that any
300-year-old pilot couldn't do.

306
00:16:50.437 --> 00:16:51.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are being scanned from the surface.

307
00:16:51.969 --> 00:16:53.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: Taking evasive maneuvers.

308
00:16:54.396 --> 00:16:55.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did they get a fix on us?

309
00:16:55.734 --> 00:16:56.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: I do not think so.

310
00:16:56.898 --> 00:16:59.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
JADZIA: Good. We've come too long a way
just to get shot down.

311
00:16:59.935 --> 00:17:02.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you take the helm,
I'll scan the surface for a landing site.

312
00:17:03.984 --> 00:17:05.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's the base...

313
00:17:05.943 --> 00:17:07.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The rendezvous point...

314
00:17:09.048 --> 00:17:10.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the Dominion sensor perimeter.

315
00:17:10.942 --> 00:17:14.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a valley about 20 kilometers
north of the rendezvous point.

316
00:17:14.341 --> 00:17:17.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a long way to go
on foot in the jungle,

317
00:17:17.097 --> 00:17:19.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I don't think we can risk taking
the ship any closer to their sensors.

318
00:17:20.175 --> 00:17:21.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Agreed.

319
00:17:30.544 --> 00:17:32.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have less than two days
to reach the rendezvous point.

320
00:17:33.485 --> 00:17:35.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
About 10 kilometers a day,
that shouldn't be too bad.

321
00:17:35.823 --> 00:17:37.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do not underestimate the task ahead.

322
00:17:37.903 --> 00:17:41.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We still have to penetrate the sensor grid
and avoid the Dominion patrols.

323
00:17:41.663 --> 00:17:42.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) I know,

324
00:17:42.522 --> 00:17:44.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
find a man in the middle
of an alien jungle,

325
00:17:44.780 --> 00:17:46.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then walk him out without getting caught.

326
00:17:46.140 --> 00:17:47.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Piece of cake.

327
00:17:47.561 --> 00:17:49.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Ready?
-After you.

328
00:18:03.876 --> 00:18:05.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
OK.

329
00:18:05.275 --> 00:18:06.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go to 25 joules.

330
00:18:14.472 --> 00:18:15.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: 25 joules.

331
00:18:18.631 --> 00:18:19.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Done.

332
00:18:19.751 --> 00:18:21.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's it. We're linked.

333
00:18:24.730 --> 00:18:25.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here, check my work.

334
00:18:27.808 --> 00:18:30.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dominion encryption lockouts bypassed,

335
00:18:30.088 --> 00:18:31.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
tricorder link to their sensor grids,

336
00:18:32.108 --> 00:18:33.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
life signs masked.

337
00:18:34.007 --> 00:18:34.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nicely done.

338
00:18:35.086 --> 00:18:36.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

339
00:18:39.694 --> 00:18:42.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of course, our tricorders
will be useless from now on.

340
00:18:43.605 --> 00:18:44.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There you go again,

341
00:18:44.345 --> 00:18:46.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
looking for the cloud
in the silver lining.

342
00:18:46.502 --> 00:18:47.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am not complaining.

343
00:18:48.942 --> 00:18:50.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I look forward to walking
through the jungle

344
00:18:50.663 --> 00:18:53.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
without a map
and no idea of what lies ahead.

345
00:18:54.430 --> 00:18:56.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, the funny thing is you probably are.

346
00:19:02.578 --> 00:19:04.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a Ferengi-only game, gentlemen.

347
00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:06.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You let Dax play.

348
00:19:06.357 --> 00:19:09.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's an exception, the only exception.

349
00:19:09.616 --> 00:19:10.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're afraid I'll clean you out.

350
00:19:11.056 --> 00:19:14.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid you'll embarrass yourself
and ruin the game for the rest of us.

351
00:19:14.494 --> 00:19:17.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I can keep up.

352
00:19:17.250 --> 00:19:18.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The question is, can you keep up with me?

353
00:19:18.873 --> 00:19:21.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't try and scare me
with that genetically engineered

354
00:19:21.075 --> 00:19:22.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
intellect of yours, Doctor.

355
00:19:23.184 --> 00:19:24.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tongo is more than just number crunching.

356
00:19:25.571 --> 00:19:27.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They have yet to create the computer
that can master this game.

357
00:19:28.279 --> 00:19:29.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then you shouldn't have
anything to worry about.

358
00:19:31.109 --> 00:19:34.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You realize we are not playing for drinks.

359
00:19:35.009 --> 00:19:36.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a high stakes game.

360
00:19:37.410 --> 00:19:38.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We came to play.

361
00:19:40.448 --> 00:19:42.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gentlemen?

362
00:19:42.288 --> 00:19:43.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

363
00:19:45.047 --> 00:19:46.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

364
00:19:46.447 --> 00:19:49.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The buy-in is five strips,
and you're dealing.

365
00:19:53.763 --> 00:19:55.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You better get off to a fast start.

366
00:19:56.602 --> 00:19:58.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They won't know what hit them.

367
00:20:03.800 --> 00:20:06.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Buy at 300, sell at 350.

368
00:20:09.475 --> 00:20:12.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're a quick study, Doctor.
I'll give you that.

369
00:20:12.358 --> 00:20:14.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean quick for a "hu-man,"
don't you, Quark?

370
00:20:14.798 --> 00:20:17.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would never say anything
so distasteful during a game.

371
00:20:17.548 --> 00:20:18.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, you'd wait until it was over.

372
00:20:19.667 --> 00:20:21.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course.

373
00:20:21.267 --> 00:20:23.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

374
00:20:25.065 --> 00:20:26.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax was a quick study too.

375
00:20:26.833 --> 00:20:28.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She told me it only took her two weeks
to win her first match.

376
00:20:28.952 --> 00:20:30.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's practically unheard of.

377
00:20:30.192 --> 00:20:32.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax specializes in the unexpected.

378
00:20:32.451 --> 00:20:34.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Still buying at 300, selling at four.

379
00:20:36.130 --> 00:20:38.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like to index the margin at 20%.

380
00:20:38.769 --> 00:20:40.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Interesting.

381
00:20:40.628 --> 00:20:43.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She certainly did the unexpected
when she married Commander Boring.

382
00:20:43.668 --> 00:20:45.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's for sure.

383
00:20:45.027 --> 00:20:47.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When they first started seeing each other,
I thought,

384
00:20:47.265 --> 00:20:50.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"This can't last. I give it two months."

385
00:20:51.264 --> 00:20:53.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll buy at 400...

386
00:20:53.583 --> 00:20:54.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And sell at five.

387
00:20:55.685 --> 00:20:56.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had the same thought.

388
00:20:56.803 --> 00:20:58.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Although, to tell you the truth,
I only gave it a month.

389
00:20:59.043 --> 00:20:59.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

390
00:21:00.523 --> 00:21:02.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's a real heart-breaker, that one.

391
00:21:04.001 --> 00:21:05.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That she is.

392
00:21:05.721 --> 00:21:08.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Leverage the buy-in and sell at 550.

393
00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:12.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know...

394
00:21:12.759 --> 00:21:15.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You go through a lot of ups and downs
in my business.

395
00:21:16.798 --> 00:21:19.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are days when the profits are down,
and the customers are scarce,

396
00:21:20.163 --> 00:21:23.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you think you'll never see
another strip of latinum again,

397
00:21:24.838 --> 00:21:27.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And then, Jadzia comes in...

398
00:21:28.441 --> 00:21:30.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And flashes that smile of hers.

399
00:21:31.276 --> 00:21:34.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Suddenly things
don't seem so bad after all.

400
00:21:34.315 --> 00:21:36.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know exactly what you mean.

401
00:21:36.714 --> 00:21:40.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know,
sometimes she walks past the infirmary,

402
00:21:40.803 --> 00:21:42.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and all she has to do is wink,
and somehow, that...

403
00:21:43.230 --> 00:21:45.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
makes my whole day look a little brighter.

404
00:21:45.871 --> 00:21:46.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Focus, Julian. Focus.

405
00:21:47.269 --> 00:21:48.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shh!

406
00:21:49.188 --> 00:21:53.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll, uh, buy that 550, and...

407
00:21:54.346 --> 00:21:55.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Index the exchange at 10.

408
00:21:56.466 --> 00:21:58.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now she's married.

409
00:21:58.226 --> 00:21:59.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Married.

410
00:21:59.465 --> 00:22:00.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Out of reach.

411
00:22:02.744 --> 00:22:03.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm converting my reserves...

412
00:22:05.023 --> 00:22:06.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And selling at 600.

413
00:22:08.223 --> 00:22:09.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know what's really sad?

414
00:22:09.982 --> 00:22:11.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What really keeps me awake at night?

415
00:22:12.621 --> 00:22:14.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's out of reach because we let her go.

416
00:22:17.259 --> 00:22:19.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, I suppose so...

417
00:22:19.428 --> 00:22:20.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But some things just weren't meant to be.

418
00:22:22.597 --> 00:22:23.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

419
00:22:23.638 --> 00:22:24.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Julian!

420
00:22:24.957 --> 00:22:26.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure you want to--

421
00:22:26.357 --> 00:22:29.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief! Please. You know the rules.

422
00:22:29.475 --> 00:22:30.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No coaching during a round.

423
00:22:35.634 --> 00:22:37.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're probably right.

424
00:22:40.213 --> 00:22:42.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But what if that's
a convenient rationalization?

425
00:22:43.652 --> 00:22:48.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if deep down in our heart of hearts,
we both know she's something unique...

426
00:22:48.331 --> 00:22:49.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Something we may never see again,

427
00:22:50.315 --> 00:22:51.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a chance at true happiness?

428
00:22:52.270 --> 00:22:54.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And we let her slip through our fingers.

429
00:22:55.410 --> 00:22:57.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if 50 years from now
we each look back

430
00:22:57.251 --> 00:22:59.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and say, "What a fool I was"?

431
00:23:04.084 --> 00:23:05.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

432
00:23:06.123 --> 00:23:07.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor?

433
00:23:07.284 --> 00:23:08.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm?

434
00:23:08.563 --> 00:23:09.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

435
00:23:09.923 --> 00:23:11.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

436
00:23:11.323 --> 00:23:12.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry. Um...

437
00:23:14.121 --> 00:23:15.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Full consortium.

438
00:23:18.800 --> 00:23:21.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Total monopoly.

439
00:23:21.359 --> 00:23:22.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What?
-( Ferengis snickering )

440
00:23:25.958 --> 00:23:27.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You seem to be out of money.

441
00:23:28.277 --> 00:23:29.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles?

442
00:23:30.197 --> 00:23:31.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're busted.

443
00:23:31.458 --> 00:23:32.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks for the game.

444
00:23:32.777 --> 00:23:34.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Welcome back anytime.

445
00:23:34.137 --> 00:23:35.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Wait.

446
00:23:35.438 --> 00:23:38.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Quark, did you really mean all that
about Dax...

447
00:23:39.615 --> 00:23:41.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Being my one last chance
for true happiness?

448
00:23:42.854 --> 00:23:47.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doctor, you don't expect me
to show you all my cards, do you?

449
00:23:49.532 --> 00:23:50.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( money rattling )

450
00:23:53.092 --> 00:23:53.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) You lost.

451
00:23:56.134 --> 00:23:56.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What ever happened to "we"?

452
00:23:56.291 --> 00:24:00.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We weren't mooning over lost love
with a Ferengi holding a total monopoly.

453
00:24:00.692 --> 00:24:02.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean all that about Dax
was meant to distract me?

454
00:24:02.588 --> 00:24:03.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Obviously.

455
00:24:04.626 --> 00:24:05.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't believe I let him get to me.

456
00:24:06.429 --> 00:24:08.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. Well... Not your fault.

457
00:24:10.246 --> 00:24:13.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Genetically engineered or not,
you're still "hu-man."

458
00:24:15.564 --> 00:24:17.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( rueful chuckling ) I guess.

459
00:24:18.203 --> 00:24:20.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Let's get a drink.
-( groaning )

460
00:24:43.835 --> 00:24:45.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device humming )

461
00:25:03.750 --> 00:25:05.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ow!

462
00:25:57.573 --> 00:25:58.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( shivering )

463
00:26:00.852 --> 00:26:03.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, let's not stand on pride, shall we?

464
00:26:03.772 --> 00:26:06.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Trills don't like the heat
and Klingons don't like the cold.

465
00:26:06.211 --> 00:26:07.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no shame in admitting it.

466
00:26:08.990 --> 00:26:09.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

467
00:26:10.070 --> 00:26:12.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're welcome.

468
00:26:12.450 --> 00:26:14.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, how are you enjoying your honeymoon?

469
00:26:14.487 --> 00:26:15.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you suffering enough?

470
00:26:16.689 --> 00:26:17.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Almost.

471
00:26:18.288 --> 00:26:19.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is there anything I can get for you?

472
00:26:21.786 --> 00:26:22.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More pain.

473
00:26:23.445 --> 00:26:24.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Less cold.

474
00:26:24.606 --> 00:26:26.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughing )

475
00:26:26.125 --> 00:26:27.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know why that's funny, but it is.

476
00:26:28.658 --> 00:26:29.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( animal howling )

477
00:26:30.404 --> 00:26:31.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mating call?

478
00:26:32.204 --> 00:26:33.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
500 meters.

479
00:26:34.442 --> 00:26:35.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That way.

480
00:26:35.882 --> 00:26:37.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

481
00:26:39.690 --> 00:26:40.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that didn't take long.

482
00:26:41.641 --> 00:26:43.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Less than 300 meters.

483
00:26:43.599 --> 00:26:45.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

484
00:26:46.399 --> 00:26:48.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) Another happy couple.

485
00:26:53.877 --> 00:26:54.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When I was a boy,

486
00:26:55.957 --> 00:26:59.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
my father used to take my brother and me
on camping trips in the Ural mountains.

487
00:27:01.695 --> 00:27:04.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every night, we would listen to the wolves
howling in the distance.

488
00:27:06.574 --> 00:27:07.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nikolai was afraid of them,

489
00:27:08.472 --> 00:27:11.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I would lay in my tent for hours,
just listening.

490
00:27:14.311 --> 00:27:17.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I remember being seized by the urge
to just rip off my clothes

491
00:27:17.654 --> 00:27:19.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and run into the night
and live in the forest,

492
00:27:20.649 --> 00:27:23.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and become something... wild.

493
00:27:25.167 --> 00:27:26.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

494
00:27:30.126 --> 00:27:31.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He must have been rejected.
He's moving away.

495
00:27:34.164 --> 00:27:35.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling and growling )

496
00:27:35.535 --> 00:27:36.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's not happy.

497
00:27:37.175 --> 00:27:38.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( twig snaps )

498
00:27:38.294 --> 00:27:39.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( growling )

499
00:27:39.934 --> 00:27:42.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What? They're getting further away,
aren't they?

500
00:27:42.183 --> 00:27:45.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but it's because
something is coming.

501
00:27:47.181 --> 00:27:47.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And it is close.

502
00:28:02.176 --> 00:28:03.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( brush rustling )

503
00:28:15.572 --> 00:28:17.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device beeping )

504
00:28:35.686 --> 00:28:37.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( yelling and grunting )

505
00:28:40.605 --> 00:28:42.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( strangled gurgling yell )

506
00:28:44.323 --> 00:28:45.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

507
00:28:45.643 --> 00:28:47.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia!

508
00:28:47.883 --> 00:28:49.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping )

509
00:28:53.081 --> 00:28:54.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping )

510
00:28:56.840 --> 00:28:58.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lie still.

511
00:28:58.120 --> 00:28:59.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I can do that.

512
00:29:01.039 --> 00:29:02.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

513
00:29:02.198 --> 00:29:03.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I have the good news first?

514
00:29:06.849 --> 00:29:08.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No vital organs were damaged.

515
00:29:08.638 --> 00:29:10.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now the bad news?

516
00:29:11.036 --> 00:29:13.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The disruptor burst
left an anti-coagulant in your system.

517
00:29:14.087 --> 00:29:15.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So you can't stop the bleeding?

518
00:29:16.526 --> 00:29:17.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

519
00:29:17.766 --> 00:29:20.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I must not have taken
the whole burst.

520
00:29:21.253 --> 00:29:22.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not hemorrhaging that bad yet.

521
00:29:24.254 --> 00:29:26.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just keep me pumped full of painkillers,
and let's be on our way.

522
00:29:26.932 --> 00:29:28.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Moving could make the bleeding worse.

523
00:29:28.612 --> 00:29:29.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Staying here isn't an option.

524
00:29:30.730 --> 00:29:32.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Someone's going to come looking for them
when they don't check in,

525
00:29:33.329 --> 00:29:35.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I'd rather take my chances on foot.

526
00:29:35.608 --> 00:29:36.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You ready?

527
00:29:38.767 --> 00:29:41.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You ready?
-Ready.

528
00:29:41.486 --> 00:29:43.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's go.

529
00:29:43.526 --> 00:29:44.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

530
00:29:59.547 --> 00:30:00.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans softly )

531
00:30:08.719 --> 00:30:11.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We are still 12 kilometers
from the rendezvous point.

532
00:30:12.180 --> 00:30:13.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And only 20 hours left.

533
00:30:14.303 --> 00:30:17.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I guess it's time
we stop having so much fun

534
00:30:17.505 --> 00:30:18.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and pick up the pace, huh?

535
00:30:19.387 --> 00:30:20.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, more plasma.

536
00:30:21.267 --> 00:30:23.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, thanks. I'm full. ( chuckles weakly )

537
00:30:24.474 --> 00:30:26.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your blood pressure
has dropped another 20%.

538
00:30:27.054 --> 00:30:28.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Love that bedside manner.

539
00:30:29.841 --> 00:30:30.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, you should have been a doctor?

540
00:30:34.652 --> 00:30:36.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your bandage will need to be changed soon.

541
00:30:37.391 --> 00:30:41.093  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I think I'd like a blue
chiffon bandage this time,

542
00:30:42.075 --> 00:30:43.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
maybe some rhinestones.

543
00:30:43.729 --> 00:30:44.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Something with a little pizazz.

544
00:30:45.268 --> 00:30:46.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is no joking matter.

545
00:30:47.050 --> 00:30:47.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You are seriously injured,

546
00:30:48.048 --> 00:30:49.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we have
a great deal of terrain to cover.

547
00:30:50.048 --> 00:30:51.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just trying to lighten the mood.

548
00:30:52.571 --> 00:30:54.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is neither the time nor the place.

549
00:30:54.886 --> 00:30:56.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What happened to that new Worf?

550
00:30:56.725 --> 00:30:58.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, the one with the sense of humor?

551
00:30:59.764 --> 00:31:01.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was a mistake.

552
00:31:01.524 --> 00:31:03.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, what is that supposed to mean?

553
00:31:03.483 --> 00:31:05.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It means if I had
not been joking with you,

554
00:31:05.505 --> 00:31:07.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would not have allowed
the Jem'Hadar to get so close.

555
00:31:08.265 --> 00:31:10.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) So this is all my fault.

556
00:31:10.784 --> 00:31:12.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

557
00:31:12.264 --> 00:31:13.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is mine.

558
00:31:14.380 --> 00:31:16.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was trying to be something I am not.

559
00:31:16.723 --> 00:31:19.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By letting down my guard,
by ignoring my duty,

560
00:31:19.304 --> 00:31:20.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I allowed my wife to be injured,

561
00:31:21.217 --> 00:31:23.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I put the entire mission in jeopardy.

562
00:31:24.337 --> 00:31:25.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It will not happen again.

563
00:31:26.296 --> 00:31:27.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's not what happened.

564
00:31:28.775 --> 00:31:32.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Without our tricorders, there's no way--
-I do not wish to debate this.

565
00:31:34.314 --> 00:31:36.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have a long way to go
and very little time.

566
00:31:37.513 --> 00:31:38.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine. Let's go.

567
00:31:39.473 --> 00:31:40.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunts )

568
00:32:06.584 --> 00:32:07.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device beeping )

569
00:32:14.542 --> 00:32:15.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ready?

570
00:32:16.382 --> 00:32:17.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( softly ) Yeah.

571
00:32:40.214 --> 00:32:41.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

572
00:32:54.370 --> 00:32:55.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

573
00:33:01.248 --> 00:33:02.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hypo.

574
00:33:09.485 --> 00:33:10.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

575
00:33:12.247 --> 00:33:14.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There. Good as new.

576
00:33:20.804 --> 00:33:22.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to change your dressing.

577
00:33:22.881 --> 00:33:25.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's four bandages in two hours.

578
00:33:26.480 --> 00:33:28.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's got to be some kind of record.

579
00:33:28.919 --> 00:33:32.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, sorry. I forgot the new rules.
Nothing funny.

580
00:33:33.327 --> 00:33:34.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Got to be serious.

581
00:33:34.438 --> 00:33:35.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Life and death.

582
00:33:36.070 --> 00:33:37.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've got a job to do.

583
00:33:41.368 --> 00:33:43.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia, I know you are tired,

584
00:33:43.815 --> 00:33:46.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we have to cover three kilometers
before nightfall. Can you do it?

585
00:33:48.385 --> 00:33:49.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As long as you got those painkillers,

586
00:33:50.693 --> 00:33:52.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll follow you
through the gates of hell, sir.

587
00:33:54.532 --> 00:33:55.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm...

588
00:33:55.412 --> 00:33:58.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, that was almost a smile.

589
00:34:01.870 --> 00:34:05.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When this mission is over,
I will smile all you want.

590
00:34:06.354 --> 00:34:07.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you promise?

591
00:34:08.387 --> 00:34:08.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I promise.

592
00:34:10.707 --> 00:34:14.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then let's finish this mission
and get out of here.

593
00:34:16.356 --> 00:34:17.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( both grunt )

594
00:34:17.345 --> 00:34:18.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoa.

595
00:34:18.944 --> 00:34:19.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

596
00:34:20.025 --> 00:34:21.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's all right, I can stand.

597
00:34:21.685 --> 00:34:22.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just help me get my balance.

598
00:34:23.044 --> 00:34:24.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Help me balance.

599
00:34:25.204 --> 00:34:26.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or maybe not.

600
00:34:27.124 --> 00:34:28.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

601
00:34:31.681 --> 00:34:33.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

602
00:34:38.395 --> 00:34:39.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

603
00:34:42.099 --> 00:34:44.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me guess. Things aren't looking up.

604
00:34:45.843 --> 00:34:47.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's been another drop
in your blood pressure.

605
00:34:47.605 --> 00:34:49.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And your neural E.D.L. readings
are erratic.

606
00:34:50.788 --> 00:34:52.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what's your prescription, doc?

607
00:34:54.306 --> 00:34:57.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Surgery... at a Starbase.

608
00:34:57.135 --> 00:34:58.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could I get a second opinion?

609
00:35:06.373 --> 00:35:09.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf, you have to go on without me...

610
00:35:10.451 --> 00:35:11.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I know that.

611
00:35:11.851 --> 00:35:13.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand.

612
00:35:13.411 --> 00:35:15.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My duty requires
that I complete the mission

613
00:35:15.603 --> 00:35:17.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
regardless of my personal feelings.

614
00:35:17.806 --> 00:35:18.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Absolutely.

615
00:35:18.486 --> 00:35:20.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're a Starfleet officer.

616
00:35:20.285 --> 00:35:22.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So am I, and I understand.

617
00:35:23.446 --> 00:35:27.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The information Lasaran has could be
potentially invaluable to the war effort.

618
00:35:27.509 --> 00:35:29.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't have to explain to me.

619
00:35:30.685 --> 00:35:31.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm hurt. You're not.

620
00:35:33.303 --> 00:35:34.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And there's a job to be done.

621
00:35:35.524 --> 00:35:36.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will be back tomorrow night.

622
00:35:39.040 --> 00:35:40.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't worry.

623
00:35:40.191 --> 00:35:41.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not going anywhere.

624
00:35:42.540 --> 00:35:45.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can have you in the stasis chamber
on the runabout in 45 hours.

625
00:35:47.498 --> 00:35:48.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No problem.

626
00:35:49.919 --> 00:35:51.028  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will leave the med kit.

627
00:35:51.270 --> 00:35:53.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Scan yourself with the tricorder
every half hour.

628
00:35:53.632 --> 00:35:55.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The plasma hypospray will be set--

629
00:35:56.155 --> 00:35:58.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I took basic first aid.
I know what I have to do.

630
00:36:03.872 --> 00:36:04.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf.

631
00:36:06.871 --> 00:36:09.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been a great two months, hasn't it?

632
00:36:13.329 --> 00:36:14.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

633
00:36:17.665 --> 00:36:20.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia, I just want to tell you how--

634
00:36:22.545 --> 00:36:23.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( whispers ) Just kiss me and go.

635
00:36:45.737 --> 00:36:46.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sobbing )

636
00:37:02.132 --> 00:37:04.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( heart beating )

637
00:37:16.128 --> 00:37:19.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beating louder )

638
00:37:44.519 --> 00:37:45.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

639
00:38:06.752 --> 00:38:08.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the word?

640
00:38:11.337 --> 00:38:12.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She is still in surgery,

641
00:38:13.119 --> 00:38:15.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but Dr. Bashir is hopeful
she will make a full recovery.

642
00:38:17.357 --> 00:38:18.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lasaran's dead.

643
00:38:19.240 --> 00:38:20.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet intelligence
intercepted a transmission

644
00:38:20.852 --> 00:38:23.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
saying that he'd been killed
trying to reenter the base at Soukara.

645
00:38:24.451 --> 00:38:26.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could you have made the rendezvous?

646
00:38:26.411 --> 00:38:28.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

647
00:38:28.173 --> 00:38:30.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-But yet you turned back to save Jadzia.
-Yes.

648
00:38:31.056 --> 00:38:33.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Were you aware that
the information that man had

649
00:38:33.078 --> 00:38:34.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
could have saved millions of lives?

650
00:38:35.998 --> 00:38:37.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

651
00:38:37.639 --> 00:38:38.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what happened?

652
00:38:40.342 --> 00:38:42.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You may not understand.
-Try me, sir.

653
00:38:45.687 --> 00:38:46.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You were at my wedding.

654
00:38:47.349 --> 00:38:49.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You heard the story
of the first two Klingon hearts

655
00:38:49.451 --> 00:38:50.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and how nothing could stand against them

656
00:38:51.223 --> 00:38:53.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and how they even destroyed
the Gods that had created them.

657
00:38:55.155 --> 00:38:56.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have heard that story since I was a boy,

658
00:38:58.078 --> 00:38:59.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I never understood it...

659
00:38:59.279 --> 00:38:59.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean really understood it...

660
00:39:02.622 --> 00:39:05.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Until I was standing in the jungle
with my heart pounding in my chest,

661
00:39:06.258 --> 00:39:08.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I found that even I could
not stand against my own heart.

662
00:39:10.420 --> 00:39:11.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had to go back.

663
00:39:12.743 --> 00:39:14.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And it did not matter
what Starfleet thought,

664
00:39:14.445 --> 00:39:15.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or what the consequences were.

665
00:39:15.766 --> 00:39:18.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was my wife and I could not leave her.

666
00:39:19.897 --> 00:39:22.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As your captain,
it is my duty to inform you

667
00:39:22.799 --> 00:39:24.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that you made the wrong choice.

668
00:39:26.253 --> 00:39:28.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think Starfleet will file
any formal charges.

669
00:39:29.936 --> 00:39:31.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even a secret court-martial
would run the risk

670
00:39:31.917 --> 00:39:34.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of revealing too much about
their intelligence operations.

671
00:39:36.156 --> 00:39:38.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this will go into your service record.

672
00:39:40.328 --> 00:39:41.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And to be completely honest,

673
00:39:43.248 --> 00:39:46.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you probably won't be offered
a command on your own after this.

674
00:39:48.873 --> 00:39:49.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand.

675
00:39:50.115 --> 00:39:51.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've also issued new orders.

676
00:39:52.297 --> 00:39:54.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You and Jadzia are not
to be assigned to a mission

677
00:39:54.539 --> 00:39:55.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
on your own ever again.

678
00:40:00.725 --> 00:40:02.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And one last thing.

679
00:40:04.387 --> 00:40:05.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As a man who had a wife...

680
00:40:08.332 --> 00:40:10.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If Jennifer had been
lying in that clearing...

681
00:40:12.436 --> 00:40:14.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wouldn't have left her either.

682
00:40:20.554 --> 00:40:21.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

683
00:40:40.747 --> 00:40:41.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey.

684
00:40:42.738 --> 00:40:43.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( whispers ) I know you.

685
00:40:45.671 --> 00:40:46.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have met.

686
00:40:47.404 --> 00:40:48.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, you're joking again.

687
00:40:50.003 --> 00:40:51.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a good sign.

688
00:40:52.563 --> 00:40:54.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you make the rendezvous?

689
00:40:55.761 --> 00:40:57.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

690
00:40:58.681 --> 00:40:59.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( softly) I could not leave you there.

691
00:41:01.384 --> 00:41:05.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not for Lasaran, not for the mission,
not for anything else.

692
00:41:06.222 --> 00:41:07.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lasaran?

693
00:41:09.462 --> 00:41:10.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dead.

694
00:41:11.744 --> 00:41:12.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you in trouble?

695
00:41:13.391 --> 00:41:14.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have been in trouble before.

696
00:41:15.984 --> 00:41:17.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

697
00:41:18.417 --> 00:41:19.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I should have kept going.

698
00:41:20.599 --> 00:41:22.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have nothing to be sorry about.

699
00:41:24.583 --> 00:41:26.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know how much your career means to you.

700
00:41:27.685 --> 00:41:28.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You come first.

701
00:41:29.930 --> 00:41:33.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Before career, before duty,
before anything.

702
00:41:35.034 --> 00:41:36.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I do not regret what I did,

703
00:41:38.028 --> 00:41:39.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I would do it again.

704
00:41:41.507 --> 00:41:43.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what to say.

705
00:41:44.986 --> 00:41:48.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You could say,
"Thank you for saving my life."

706
00:41:50.704 --> 00:41:52.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you for saving my life.

707
00:41:54.086 --> 00:41:57.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you could say,
"I would do the same for you, Worf."

708
00:41:57.925 --> 00:42:01.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... I'd have to think about that.

709
00:42:02.347 --> 00:42:04.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My career is very important to me,
you know.

710
00:42:06.105 --> 00:42:08.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

711
00:42:10.264 --> 00:42:12.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you could say, "I love you."

712
00:42:15.863 --> 00:42:17.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love you.

713
00:42:18.902 --> 00:42:20.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I love you.

